cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper deals with the medium access control (MAC) protocol for full-duplex networks, which is a subfield of network communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and optimization, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The evaluation of the proposed protocol involves multimedia traffic, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a distributed protocol, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with interference and security issues, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
